1
00:01:18,200 --> 00:01:21,431
I was Flint's first mate
that voyage...

2
00:01:21,520 --> 00:01:24,592
three days east of Tortola
in the Caribie.

3
00:01:24,680 --> 00:01:27,035
Flint knew an island.

4
00:01:27,120 --> 00:01:29,111
That's where we buried
the treasure.

5
00:01:29,200 --> 00:01:33,273
Gold and blood,
they were Flint's trademarks.

6
00:01:33,360 --> 00:01:36,238
He'd leave both
behind him that day.

7
00:01:40,400 --> 00:01:43,995
<i>Shiver my timbers</i>
<i>Shiver my soul</i>

8
00:01:44,080 --> 00:01:47,117
<i>Yo ho, heave ho</i>

9
00:01:47,200 --> 00:01:51,352
<i>There are men whose hearts</i>
<i>are as black as coal</i>

10
00:01:51,440 --> 00:01:53,908
<i>Yo ho, heave ho</i>

11
00:01:54,000 --> 00:01:57,549
<i>And they sailed their ship</i>
<i>'cross the ocean blue</i>

12
00:01:57,640 --> 00:02:00,632
<i>A bloodthirsty captain</i>
<i>and a cutthroat crew</i>

13
00:02:00,720 --> 00:02:04,315
<i>It's as dark a tale</i>
<i>as was ever told</i>

14
00:02:04,400 --> 00:02:09,520
<i>Of the lust for treasure</i>
<i>and the love of gold</i>

15
00:02:09,600 --> 00:02:13,832
<i>Shiver my timbers</i>
<i>Shiver my sides</i>

16
00:02:13,920 --> 00:02:16,275
<i>Yo ho, heave ho</i>

17
00:02:16,360 --> 00:02:19,989
<i>There are hungers as strong</i>
<i>as the winds and tides</i>

18
00:02:20,080 --> 00:02:22,878
<i>Yo ho, heave ho</i>

19
00:02:22,960 --> 00:02:26,714
<i>And those buccaneers</i>
<i>drown their sins in rum</i>

20
00:02:26,800 --> 00:02:30,076
<i>The devil himself would</i>
<i>have to call them scum</i>

21
00:02:30,160 --> 00:02:33,596
<i>Every man aboard would have</i>
<i>killed his mate</i>

22
00:02:33,680 --> 00:02:37,229
<i>For a bag of guineas</i>
<i>or a piece of eight</i>

23
00:02:37,320 --> 00:02:39,151
<i>A piece of eight</i>

24
00:02:39,240 --> 00:02:42,710
<i>-A piece of eight</i>
<i>-A five, six, seven, eight</i>

25
00:02:42,800 --> 00:02:45,598
<i>Hulla wacka, ulla wacka</i>
<i>Something not right</i>

26
00:02:45,680 --> 00:02:49,434
<i>Many wicked icky things</i>
<i>gonna happen tonight</i>

27
00:02:49,520 --> 00:02:51,988
<i>Hulla wacka, moolah wacka</i>
<i>Sailor man beware</i>

28
00:02:52,080 --> 00:02:56,073
<i>When de money in de ground</i>
<i>Dere's murder in de air</i>

29
00:02:56,160 --> 00:02:57,991
<i>Murder in the air</i>

30
00:02:58,080 --> 00:02:59,832
One more time now.

31
00:02:59,920 --> 00:03:02,878
<i>Shiver my timbers</i>
<i>Shiver my bones</i>

32
00:03:02,960 --> 00:03:06,236
<i>Yo ho, heave ho</i>

33
00:03:06,320 --> 00:03:10,632
<i>There are secrets that sleep</i>
<i>with old Davy Jones</i>

34
00:03:10,720 --> 00:03:12,950
<i>Yo ho, heave ho</i>

35
00:03:13,040 --> 00:03:16,316
<i>When the mainsail's set</i>
<i>and the anchor's weighed</i>

36
00:03:16,400 --> 00:03:19,995
<i>There's no turning back</i>
<i>from any course that's laid</i>

37
00:03:20,080 --> 00:03:23,675
<i>And when greed and villainy</i>
<i>sail the sea</i>

38
00:03:23,760 --> 00:03:28,959
<i>You can bet your boots</i>
<i>there'll be treachery</i>

39
00:03:37,640 --> 00:03:40,950
<i>Shiver my timbers</i>
<i>Shiver my sails</i>

40
00:03:41,040 --> 00:03:43,429
<i>Dead men tell no tales</i>

41
00:03:45,680 --> 00:03:49,434
Oh, aye. Fifteen men
went ashore that day...

42
00:03:49,520 --> 00:03:53,308
and only Flint, his own self,
returned.

43
00:03:53,800 --> 00:03:56,155
Oh, aye, and then old Flinty...

44
00:03:56,240 --> 00:04:00,313
up and died afore they could get
back to that cursed island...

45
00:04:00,400 --> 00:04:02,630
and dig up the treasure.

46
00:04:02,720 --> 00:04:07,191
No one knows to this day
who has old Flint's map.

47
00:04:07,280 --> 00:04:10,556
Now, isn't that a story
worth the hearing?

48
00:04:10,640 --> 00:04:13,279
It was the first dozen
times we heard it.

49
00:04:13,360 --> 00:04:15,999
I'll drink to that.

50
00:04:16,080 --> 00:04:19,038
But who has
the map now, huh?

51
00:04:19,120 --> 00:04:22,829
Some black-hearted,
squid-suckin' buccaneer?

52
00:04:22,920 --> 00:04:26,549
Or maybe it's
our very own Jim Hawkins.

53
00:04:26,640 --> 00:04:28,471
Eh,Jimmy?

54
00:04:28,560 --> 00:04:31,518
If I had it, my friends and I wouldn't
be here serving you rum, Mr Bones.

55
00:04:31,600 --> 00:04:33,989
That's right. We'd be out
searching for that treasure...

56
00:04:34,080 --> 00:04:36,913
sailing the seven seas
on a five-year mission...

57
00:04:37,000 --> 00:04:40,072
boldly going where no man
has gone before.

58
00:04:40,160 --> 00:04:42,390
- Say, that's catchy.
- Huh. Not me.

59
00:04:42,480 --> 00:04:46,473
If I had that treasure map,
I'd be tradin' it for a decent meal.

60
00:04:46,560 --> 00:04:48,790
Hey, Gonzo, you think
he's gonna eat this?

61
00:04:48,880 --> 00:04:52,953
Aye! Beware the one-legged man!
He's the one to fear!

62
00:04:53,040 --> 00:04:54,712
Don't worry, Captain.
We'll watch for him.

63
00:04:54,800 --> 00:04:57,519
Yeah, I'll watch for him,
if he's deliverin' a pizza.

64
00:04:59,360 --> 00:05:01,271
Even old Flinty
feared him.

65
00:05:01,360 --> 00:05:05,114
If he comes pokin' 'round here,
you run for me whippety-quick!

66
00:05:05,200 --> 00:05:07,760
- If we see him, we'll tell you.
- Yeah. One leg, three heads...

67
00:05:07,840 --> 00:05:09,671
couple of dozen noses--
if anything weird happens--

68
00:05:09,760 --> 00:05:12,797
And it'll be nay
jokin' matter, hose nose.

69
00:05:12,880 --> 00:05:15,838
The one-legged man
brings death.

70
00:05:15,920 --> 00:05:18,229
Time, gentlemen!

71
00:05:18,320 --> 00:05:20,151
It's closing time!

72
00:05:20,240 --> 00:05:22,390
Ya pays your bills,
and then ya shove off.

73
00:05:22,480 --> 00:05:24,436
Go on. Out ya go!

74
00:05:26,880 --> 00:05:29,189
Oh, you're drunk again,
are ya?

75
00:05:29,280 --> 00:05:32,158
Boys, look at the state
of this place!

76
00:05:32,240 --> 00:05:34,549
How comes it gets to be
such a pigsty, huh?

77
00:05:34,640 --> 00:05:36,471
Pigsty? Hey!

78
00:05:36,560 --> 00:05:38,710
No offence meant, gentlemen, sirs.
No offence meant.

79
00:05:38,800 --> 00:05:41,030
- Here's to you, boys!
- Time!

80
00:05:41,120 --> 00:05:43,190
- I'm away to my room.
- Thank you, Mr Bones.

81
00:05:43,280 --> 00:05:44,633
- Thank you, Bill.
- There you go!

82
00:05:44,720 --> 00:05:47,632
Don't forget to come back tomorrow
for our lunchtime special:

83
00:05:47,720 --> 00:05:49,597
- roast suckling--
- Huh?

84
00:05:49,680 --> 00:05:52,274
- Potatoes, sir. Potatoes.
- All right.

85
00:05:52,360 --> 00:05:55,193
No-- No offence, madam.
No offence.

86
00:05:57,520 --> 00:05:59,670
All right, boys.

87
00:05:59,760 --> 00:06:02,320
When you're finished here,
you can go and clean up in the kitchen.

88
00:06:02,400 --> 00:06:05,119
I left some table scraps
in there for your supper.

89
00:06:05,200 --> 00:06:07,760
Oh, yes, and, boys...

90
00:06:07,840 --> 00:06:10,400
last night you forgot
to put out the lantern!

91
00:06:10,480 --> 00:06:15,190
If you forget that again,
there'll be no table scraps for a week!

92
00:06:16,480 --> 00:06:18,869
You're standing on my ear.

93
00:06:18,960 --> 00:06:20,951
Easy. Whoa, whoa, whoa!
Easy, Rizzo!

94
00:06:21,040 --> 00:06:23,952
Whoa, whoa, whoa!
That's it. Steady.

95
00:06:24,040 --> 00:06:27,032
- I hate my life.
- I hate your life too.

96
00:06:27,120 --> 00:06:30,954
- If I had a life, I'd hate it.
- I should just run off to sea

97
00:06:31,040 --> 00:06:34,635
He was my age when he sailed
to China as a cabin boy

98
00:06:34,720 --> 00:06:36,631
Run off to sea
and just leave everybody?

99
00:06:36,720 --> 00:06:39,359
Who's everybody?
I'm an orphan. I've got no family.

100
00:06:39,440 --> 00:06:42,557
- Hey, you got us!
- Yeah, we're family. Got it.

101
00:06:47,520 --> 00:06:51,798
I mean, some family we are. Be serious,
Rizzo. We don't exactly look alike.

102
00:06:51,880 --> 00:06:56,954
Okay, all right. So I'm a rat and you're
a human being and Gonzo's a, uh--

103
00:06:57,040 --> 00:06:59,508
- Whatever.
- Yeah. We're still family.

104
00:06:59,600 --> 00:07:02,353
- Yeah.
- But I wish my life were more like...

105
00:07:02,440 --> 00:07:04,158
one of Captain Bones'
adventures...

106
00:07:04,240 --> 00:07:06,708
sailing the high seas and
searching for buried treasure.

107
00:07:06,800 --> 00:07:10,679
Yeah, discovering lost islands
and weird civilizations.

108
00:07:10,760 --> 00:07:13,911
Navigating with my father's old compass
to wherever the wind may take us.

109
00:07:14,000 --> 00:07:17,436
- Off to Zanzibar
to meet the Zanzibarbarians.

110
00:07:17,520 --> 00:07:19,590
To the southwest,
pirate galleons!

111
00:07:19,680 --> 00:07:22,877
To the southeast, multi-armed
Zanzibanian shark women...

112
00:07:22,960 --> 00:07:24,951
and their exploding wigs
of death!

113
00:07:25,040 --> 00:07:27,679
To the northwest,
dirty dishes!

114
00:07:27,760 --> 00:07:29,591
How does she do that?

115
00:07:29,680 --> 00:07:32,717
- Might as well start. I'll wash.
- Oh, yeah. I'll dry.

116
00:07:32,800 --> 00:07:34,597
I'll break.

117
00:07:38,520 --> 00:07:41,910
<i>I look around here</i>
<i>and I want to cry</i>

118
00:07:42,000 --> 00:07:43,831
Me too. Yeah.

119
00:07:43,920 --> 00:07:46,992
<i>I feel like the world</i>
<i>is passing me by</i>

120
00:07:47,080 --> 00:07:48,433
It is.

121
00:07:48,520 --> 00:07:50,954
<i>And I just can't</i>
<i>help but wonder</i>

122
00:07:51,040 --> 00:07:53,429
<i>Am I doomed to wash and dry</i>

123
00:07:53,520 --> 00:07:58,719
<i>And is it a curse I'm under</i>
<i>to do it till I die</i>

124
00:07:58,800 --> 00:08:01,268
- Oh, I hope not.
- Yeah.

125
00:08:01,360 --> 00:08:03,749
<i>- When I could be an explorer</i>
- Sure ya could.

126
00:08:03,840 --> 00:08:05,990
<i>- Sailing off to distant lands</i>
- Not so fast.

127
00:08:06,080 --> 00:08:07,911
<i>Instead of spending</i>
<i>every afternoon</i>

128
00:08:08,000 --> 00:08:10,070
<i>Just getting dishpan hands</i>

129
00:08:10,160 --> 00:08:14,392
<i>My future looks like nowhere</i>
<i>that I want to be</i>

130
00:08:14,480 --> 00:08:17,517
<i>There's gotta be</i>
<i>something better</i>

131
00:08:17,600 --> 00:08:19,033
<i>Something better</i>

132
00:08:19,120 --> 00:08:23,193
<i>There's gotta be something</i>
<i>better than this for me</i>

133
00:08:23,280 --> 00:08:24,918
Well, now you're talkin'.

134
00:08:25,000 --> 00:08:29,073
<i>If it's weird and wild</i>
<i>let's go and find it</i>

135
00:08:29,160 --> 00:08:31,913
<i>The crazier, the better</i>
<i>is what I say</i>

136
00:08:32,000 --> 00:08:33,399
Yeah, that's true.

137
00:08:33,480 --> 00:08:36,517
<i>To tell the truth</i>
<i>I really wouldn't mind it</i>

138
00:08:36,600 --> 00:08:37,510
Mind what?

139
00:08:37,600 --> 00:08:42,674
<i>If we found someplace</i>
<i>with ten square meals a day</i>

140
00:08:42,760 --> 00:08:44,591
<i>Let danger call my name</i>

141
00:08:44,680 --> 00:08:47,114
<i>If it does</i>
<i>I'm gonna hide</i>

142
00:08:47,200 --> 00:08:50,158
<i>I'll put my courage</i>
<i>to the test</i>

143
00:08:50,240 --> 00:08:52,310
<i>And I'll be</i>
<i>by your side</i>

144
00:08:52,400 --> 00:08:54,391
<i>He'll be by your side</i>

145
00:08:54,480 --> 00:08:59,554
<i>There's gotta be</i>
<i>something better than this</i>

146
00:08:59,640 --> 00:09:03,155
<i>- Something more than this</i>
<i>- I know that there's so much out there</i>

147
00:09:03,240 --> 00:09:06,073
<i>- To see</i>
<i>- To see</i>

148
00:09:06,160 --> 00:09:08,310
<i>And I know</i>
<i>this life I'm living</i>

149
00:09:08,400 --> 00:09:12,393
<i>Can't be my destiny</i>

150
00:09:12,480 --> 00:09:16,109
<i>There's gotta be</i>
<i>something better</i>

151
00:09:16,200 --> 00:09:17,918
<i>Something better</i>

152
00:09:18,000 --> 00:09:21,709
<i>There's gotta be something</i>
<i>better than this for me</i>

153
00:09:21,800 --> 00:09:25,190
- And me!
- Wait a minute. What about me?

154
00:09:25,280 --> 00:09:30,070
<i>There's something better</i>
<i>than this for you and</i>

155
00:09:30,160 --> 00:09:40,400
<i>Me</i>

156
00:09:40,480 --> 00:09:42,596
Enough of this singin'!

157
00:09:42,760 --> 00:09:45,433
Rum! I need rum, lads!

158
00:09:45,520 --> 00:09:48,830
I got the horrors!
Give me rum!

159
00:09:48,920 --> 00:09:50,558
Rum till I float!

160
00:09:50,640 --> 00:09:53,757
All right! All right!
Just one small one.

161
00:09:53,840 --> 00:09:56,479
Don't be giving him
any more rum!

162
00:09:56,560 --> 00:09:59,916
How does she blooming do that?

163
00:10:00,000 --> 00:10:01,274
Shh! Shh!

164
00:10:23,760 --> 00:10:29,118
Billy Bones!
It's me, Blind Pew.

165
00:10:29,200 --> 00:10:32,590
I know you're here, Billy.

166
00:10:32,680 --> 00:10:35,353
Ya snivelling coward!

167
00:10:35,440 --> 00:10:38,318
It's some kind
of a blind fiend.

168
00:10:38,400 --> 00:10:40,311
I believe they prefer
''visually challenged fiend.''

169
00:10:40,400 --> 00:10:45,190
Ah, I heard that!
There's someone here!

170
00:10:45,280 --> 00:10:47,510
Uh, no. Over here!

171
00:10:50,320 --> 00:10:52,231
Hmm, over here.

172
00:10:56,400 --> 00:11:00,075
Billy Bones! Ah,
I'd know that scurvy mug...

173
00:11:00,160 --> 00:11:03,197
of yours anywhere.

174
00:11:03,280 --> 00:11:05,191
Excuse me, sir,
but the bar is closed.

175
00:11:07,240 --> 00:11:11,199
Aha. A pretty
little girl, is it?

176
00:11:11,280 --> 00:11:15,193
Yes. Take me
to Billy Bones, my pet.

177
00:11:15,280 --> 00:11:16,952
Y-You've come
to the wrong place.

178
00:11:17,040 --> 00:11:19,918
Th-There's no Billy Bones here,
and I'm not a girl.

179
00:11:20,000 --> 00:11:25,120
Oh, I may be visually challenged,
but I can see you're lying.

180
00:11:25,200 --> 00:11:26,952
Huh?

181
00:11:28,880 --> 00:11:33,192
Good evening, Bill.
I know it's you.

182
00:11:33,280 --> 00:11:37,831
Yes. You thought you could
get away with it, didn't you?

183
00:11:37,920 --> 00:11:40,434
Just take it all
for yourself...

184
00:11:40,520 --> 00:11:44,718
and leave your shipmates
with nothing.

185
00:11:44,800 --> 00:11:48,429
We're not pleased with that,
Bill. Not at all.

186
00:11:48,520 --> 00:11:52,798
We want you to have this!

187
00:12:06,920 --> 00:12:09,150
Watch where you're going,
you stupid cat!

188
00:12:23,920 --> 00:12:26,309
The Black Spot!

189
00:12:34,960 --> 00:12:37,758
But I don't understand.
What is the Black Spot?

190
00:12:37,840 --> 00:12:40,400
The Black Spot's
a pirate's death sentence!

191
00:12:40,480 --> 00:12:44,473
- Fabulous.
- They'll be comin' to kill me tonight!

192
00:12:44,560 --> 00:12:46,391
- We'd better help.
- Yeah, yeah, let's get some stuff.

193
00:12:46,480 --> 00:12:49,916
- It's my sea chest them lubbers want.
- Underwear.

194
00:12:50,000 --> 00:12:53,913
But I'll trick them! I'll shake out
another reef and daddle 'em again!

195
00:12:54,000 --> 00:12:57,197
You wanna run that by us again
in English, Mr Bones?

196
00:12:57,280 --> 00:12:59,589
It's mine! I'm goin'
for that treasure myself!

197
00:12:59,680 --> 00:13:02,990
And no one-legged
son of a bilge rat will--

198
00:13:05,720 --> 00:13:06,869
Captain Bones!

199
00:13:08,360 --> 00:13:13,070
He died? And this is supposed
to be a kids' movie.

200
00:13:13,160 --> 00:13:16,232
Jimmy.Jim.
Jimmy,Jim,Jim,Jim,Jim.

201
00:13:16,320 --> 00:13:19,198
You always been a decent sort
to old Billy Bones.

202
00:13:19,280 --> 00:13:21,589
But I'm not Jimmy,Jim,Jimmy,
Jim,Jim,Jim,Jim.

203
00:13:21,680 --> 00:13:24,319
He's Jimmy,Jim,Jimmy,
Jim,Jim,Jim,Jim.

204
00:13:24,400 --> 00:13:25,833
-Jim!
- Yes, Captain.

205
00:13:25,920 --> 00:13:28,229
Jim,Jimmy,Jimmy,Jim,
Jim,Jim,Jim.

206
00:13:28,320 --> 00:13:30,550
- Yes, Captain. What is it?
- Take the map!

207
00:13:30,640 --> 00:13:32,949
- What map?
- The map to old Flint's treasure!

208
00:13:33,040 --> 00:13:34,871
Don't ya understand
what I been tellin' ya?

209
00:13:34,960 --> 00:13:38,236
I was Flinty's first mate!
We all were! Blind Pew and me!

210
00:13:38,320 --> 00:13:40,311
Me own shipmates,
they'll gully me for sure!

211
00:13:40,400 --> 00:13:42,356
And anybody else to get
their mitts on that map!

212
00:13:42,440 --> 00:13:44,476
A-And gullying hurts, right?

213
00:13:44,560 --> 00:13:46,516
Oh, aye! A lot!

214
00:13:46,600 --> 00:13:49,433
- So quick.
- Go to my sea chest! Get the map!

215
00:13:49,520 --> 00:13:51,397
Oh, yeah.

216
00:13:51,480 --> 00:13:55,439
- Oh, there. There.
- Oh, I think I've-- Oh, no.

217
00:13:55,520 --> 00:13:58,478
- Hey, guys, look!
- Rizzo!

218
00:13:58,560 --> 00:14:00,391
Oh, here!
How about this?

219
00:14:00,480 --> 00:14:02,391
Let's see.

220
00:14:04,520 --> 00:14:06,795
Hey, Rizzo, look.

221
00:14:13,600 --> 00:14:16,956
- It is a treasure map.
- We're gonna be rich.

222
00:14:17,040 --> 00:14:18,871
- We're gonna be dead.
- Beware, lads!

223
00:14:18,960 --> 00:14:20,951
Beware!

224
00:14:21,040 --> 00:14:23,508
- What? The one-legged man?
- Aye! But also...

225
00:14:23,600 --> 00:14:27,912
beware runnin' with scissors
or any other pointy objects.

226
00:14:28,000 --> 00:14:32,630
It's all good fun till
somebody loses an--

227
00:14:33,840 --> 00:14:35,671
Captain?

228
00:14:37,280 --> 00:14:40,317
We're standing in a room
with a dead guy!

229
00:14:45,720 --> 00:14:47,631
Jim!

230
00:14:56,880 --> 00:15:01,556
Oh, Billy Bones!
Trick or treat!

231
00:15:03,680 --> 00:15:05,989
Don't try to hide, Billy!
You know what we want!

232
00:15:13,160 --> 00:15:17,199
Where are ya, Billy Bones?
Where are ya, Billy?

233
00:15:18,880 --> 00:15:20,632
Mrs Bluveridge!

234
00:15:20,720 --> 00:15:24,554
There's no use in hiding!

235
00:15:24,640 --> 00:15:27,279
Can't a woman get her
beauty sleep any more?

236
00:15:28,400 --> 00:15:30,709
Jim, what you doing?

237
00:15:32,680 --> 00:15:34,875
Aha! Aha!

238
00:15:34,960 --> 00:15:37,793
Oh! Voila!

239
00:15:41,280 --> 00:15:43,510
- Okay, okay. I found the gun.
- Oh, now we gotta load it.

240
00:15:43,600 --> 00:15:46,068
- Okay.
- Oops.

241
00:15:47,920 --> 00:15:50,229
Okay, where does Mrs Bluveridge
keep the bullets?

242
00:15:50,320 --> 00:15:54,552
Billy's dead, and he hasn't
got the blooming map!

243
00:15:54,640 --> 00:15:57,108
- Those little girls must have it.
- Yeah!

244
00:15:57,200 --> 00:15:59,031
- Get them!
- Yeah!

245
00:15:59,120 --> 00:16:00,951
- Gonzo! Gonzo!
- What? What?

246
00:16:01,040 --> 00:16:03,918
I found the bullets. See?
Here they are. They--

247
00:16:04,000 --> 00:16:05,911
Oops.

248
00:16:06,000 --> 00:16:08,639
Open up in there!
We wants the map...

249
00:16:08,720 --> 00:16:11,598
and we'll skewer anybody
who gets in the way!

250
00:16:11,680 --> 00:16:14,353
Quick,Jim! The back stairs!

251
00:16:14,440 --> 00:16:16,271
Come on.

252
00:16:16,360 --> 00:16:17,918
Run! Run!

253
00:16:24,680 --> 00:16:27,592
Get out of my inn,
you tattooed miseries!

254
00:16:29,680 --> 00:16:31,989
Can't a woman
get a night's sleep alone?

255
00:16:32,080 --> 00:16:34,036
You come here, you!

256
00:16:36,280 --> 00:16:37,998
This gun is useless!

257
00:16:38,080 --> 00:16:42,198
- You lost all the bullets!
- Well, you're losin' the powder.

258
00:16:42,280 --> 00:16:44,794
The map!
Tell us where it is or die!

259
00:16:46,960 --> 00:16:48,791
- Get them!
- Run! Run, run, run!

260
00:16:53,280 --> 00:16:55,157
Hurry! Hurry!

261
00:16:55,240 --> 00:16:57,356
Hurry!

262
00:17:01,640 --> 00:17:03,756
Outta the way! Outta the way!
Get outta the way!

263
00:17:11,520 --> 00:17:12,999
Stop!

264
00:17:14,840 --> 00:17:17,638
Oh, Woof.

265
00:17:25,480 --> 00:17:27,948
Geronimo!

266
00:17:28,040 --> 00:17:29,109
Guys!

267
00:17:29,200 --> 00:17:30,838
Wow! What an exit!

268
00:17:30,920 --> 00:17:32,751
- Right through a brick wall!
- I am in such pain.

269
00:17:32,840 --> 00:17:34,876
Come on!

270
00:17:34,960 --> 00:17:39,829
I think I smell
something burning, no?

271
00:17:39,920 --> 00:17:42,036
What are we gonna do?
What are we gonna do?

272
00:17:43,240 --> 00:17:45,754
We can't go home, so--

273
00:17:47,160 --> 00:17:50,869
Oh, no. Uh-uh. No way. You're not
taking me on some crazy treasure hunt.

274
00:17:50,960 --> 00:17:53,679
- I am staying right here!
- Oh, good idea, Rizzo.

275
00:17:53,760 --> 00:17:56,638
Then you can see what half-burned,
vicious pirates look like.

276
00:17:56,720 --> 00:17:59,280
What are we waitin' for?
Gimme that map. Come on. Let's go.

277
00:17:59,360 --> 00:18:02,079
Wait a minute.
What about Mrs Bluveridge?

278
00:18:04,200 --> 00:18:06,555
I'll be fine, boys!
Run for it!

279
00:18:08,160 --> 00:18:10,549
How does she do that?

280
00:18:12,160 --> 00:18:14,071
Who's gonna clean
all this up?

281
00:18:16,640 --> 00:18:18,790
Two for a penny, sir?

282
00:18:18,880 --> 00:18:23,317
- I don't want a baked potato.
- Lovely hot baked potatoes.

283
00:18:25,360 --> 00:18:28,397
- Oh, let's see.
- What a night.

284
00:18:28,480 --> 00:18:30,550
- There it is!
- Huh? Oh.

285
00:18:32,920 --> 00:18:35,753
''Trelawny & Son
Master Ship Builders''

286
00:18:39,240 --> 00:18:41,595
Whoa, whoa!
Reality check here, guys!

287
00:18:41,680 --> 00:18:43,671
Do we actually believe some
bozo's gonna give us a ship...

288
00:18:43,760 --> 00:18:45,591
just because we show him
Captain Bones' map?

289
00:18:45,680 --> 00:18:50,834
- It's worth a try, Rizzo.
- I don't know.

290
00:18:50,920 --> 00:18:52,478
May I help you?

291
00:18:52,560 --> 00:18:56,997
Yes. Thank you. We wish to speak
with Squire Trelawney, the shipbuilder.

292
00:18:57,080 --> 00:18:59,036
- We need a ship.
- Ah, I'm sorry.

293
00:18:59,120 --> 00:19:02,317
The squire's in Long Neddry
for the grouse season.

294
00:19:02,400 --> 00:19:06,393
He will return
on the feast of St Lulu.

295
00:19:07,520 --> 00:19:09,431
- Thank you.
- That's that.

296
00:19:09,520 --> 00:19:11,431
Of course, his rich...

297
00:19:11,520 --> 00:19:16,230
half-wit son
young Squire Trelawney's here.

298
00:19:16,320 --> 00:19:18,788
We'll see him, then.

299
00:19:20,200 --> 00:19:21,872
Well, gentlemen...

300
00:19:21,960 --> 00:19:25,748
this is definitely a genuine,
bona fide treasure map.

301
00:19:27,080 --> 00:19:27,990
Really!

302
00:19:28,080 --> 00:19:29,752
Yes. Mr Bimbo told me so.

303
00:19:31,720 --> 00:19:36,396
Oh, Mr Bimbo lives in my finger.
He's very smart. He's been to the moon.

304
00:19:37,360 --> 00:19:38,873
Thank you. Twice.

305
00:19:40,280 --> 00:19:42,350
- I smell a bozo.
- Mm-hmm.

306
00:19:48,920 --> 00:19:51,275
Well done, Beakie.

307
00:19:51,360 --> 00:19:53,920
Now we know that is definitely
too much gunpowder.

308
00:19:55,400 --> 00:19:59,029
Beaker, stop fooling around.
We've got company.

309
00:20:01,760 --> 00:20:05,753
Oh, hello, chappies. Everyone, this is
Dr Livesey and his assistant, Beaker.

310
00:20:05,840 --> 00:20:08,149
They do research
and development for my papa.

311
00:20:08,240 --> 00:20:09,593
Hello.

312
00:20:09,680 --> 00:20:11,830
Actually, Squire, we were
hoping to meet your father.

313
00:20:11,920 --> 00:20:16,152
- We need a ship for an ocean voyage.
- Ocean? Ocean.

314
00:20:16,240 --> 00:20:21,189
- Ocean?
- You know, the ocean?

315
00:20:22,200 --> 00:20:25,795
Oh! Th-The big,
blue, wet thing! Yes!

316
00:20:26,800 --> 00:20:29,030
Say, I know
what's happening here.

317
00:20:29,120 --> 00:20:32,396
You chaps are planning
to sail to this island, aren't you?

318
00:20:32,480 --> 00:20:35,438
- To dig up this treasure.
- Yes, but we must be quiet about it.

319
00:20:35,520 --> 00:20:38,159
- There are pirates
looking for this map.

320
00:20:38,240 --> 00:20:40,470
Isn't that exciting?

321
00:20:40,560 --> 00:20:43,677
Pirates, eh?
Well, that settles it.

322
00:20:43,760 --> 00:20:45,591
We'll use one
of my daddy's boats...

323
00:20:45,680 --> 00:20:49,673
and I will personally finance
the voyage for the treasure myself.

324
00:20:49,760 --> 00:20:54,709
- You'll do that? Really?
- What are rich, half-wit sons for?

325
00:21:00,560 --> 00:21:02,869
Well, here's the dock.
Jim, where's our boat?

326
00:21:02,960 --> 00:21:04,951
We're on a dock?
No wonder I'm seasick.

327
00:21:05,040 --> 00:21:07,679
- Ahoy!
- Ah, morning, Squire.

328
00:21:07,760 --> 00:21:11,196
Welcome. Welcome.
Ah, there she is:

329
00:21:11,280 --> 00:21:13,236
the <i>Hispaniola</i>.

330
00:21:15,240 --> 00:21:17,151
Wow!

331
00:21:18,800 --> 00:21:22,076
- Come on. Let's go!
- Yeah, let's go.

332
00:21:29,680 --> 00:21:32,558
- ''Take a cruise,'' you said.
- Huh?

333
00:21:32,640 --> 00:21:35,108
- ''See the world,'' you said.
- Huh?

334
00:21:35,200 --> 00:21:39,034
Now here we are stuck
on the front of this stupid ship.

335
00:21:39,120 --> 00:21:42,908
Well, it could be worse.
We could be stuck in the audience.

336
00:21:44,480 --> 00:21:45,913
Well, Mr Bimbo...

337
00:21:46,000 --> 00:21:48,150
the ship is provisioned,
the crew is in place...

338
00:21:48,240 --> 00:21:50,879
and the captain should be
on board within the hour.

339
00:21:50,960 --> 00:21:52,871
You have been
a busy little man.

340
00:21:52,960 --> 00:21:56,953
- Oh, look, there goes Jim.
- Oh, yeah, yeah.

341
00:21:57,040 --> 00:21:59,508
Ooh! Ooh, look!

342
00:21:59,600 --> 00:22:01,511
It's the boat
steering thing.

343
00:22:01,600 --> 00:22:03,511
This is called the helm.

344
00:22:03,600 --> 00:22:07,513
Hey, how does it feel,
Captain Hawkins?

345
00:22:07,600 --> 00:22:09,909
Feels like
we're really doing it.

346
00:22:10,000 --> 00:22:12,958
It feels like we're finally
having an adventure!

347
00:22:13,040 --> 00:22:15,679
Yeah. I'm starvin'.
Where's the kitchen?

348
00:22:17,320 --> 00:22:19,038
<i>Heigh ho and up she rises</i>

349
00:22:19,120 --> 00:22:22,237
- Something smells good.
<i>- Heigh ho and up she rises</i>

350
00:22:22,320 --> 00:22:24,788
- Cool.
<i>- Heigh ho and up she rises</i>

351
00:22:24,880 --> 00:22:28,475
<i>Early in the morning</i>

352
00:22:28,560 --> 00:22:31,472
<i>Put him in the longboat</i>
<i>until he's sober</i>

353
00:22:31,560 --> 00:22:34,677
<i>Put him in the longboat</i>
<i>till he's sober</i>

354
00:22:34,760 --> 00:22:37,274
<i>Put him in the longboat</i>
<i>till he's sober</i>

355
00:22:37,360 --> 00:22:39,191
<i>Early in the morning</i>

356
00:22:39,280 --> 00:22:42,397
What have we here?
Stowaways!

357
00:22:42,480 --> 00:22:46,712
I'm afraid we shish-kebab
and barbecue stowaways on this ship.

358
00:22:55,720 --> 00:22:57,995
Wait. I know.
You must be the cabin boys.

359
00:22:58,080 --> 00:23:01,117
- Yeah.
- Hungry, lads?

360
00:23:01,200 --> 00:23:04,317
Well, in my galley, you're always
welcome to help yourselves!

361
00:23:04,400 --> 00:23:06,709
Yes! Thank you!

362
00:23:09,000 --> 00:23:11,992
Oh, yes!

363
00:23:12,080 --> 00:23:15,152
Well, he's got a healthy appetite.
How about you, funny face?

364
00:23:15,240 --> 00:23:17,071
- Huh?
- Here.

365
00:23:17,160 --> 00:23:19,435
Hey. Thank you.

366
00:23:19,520 --> 00:23:21,909
My name is Gonzo,
and the guy in your chicken is Rizzo.

367
00:23:24,880 --> 00:23:29,112
- And you must be Master Hawkins.
- Yes, sir.

368
00:23:29,200 --> 00:23:32,636
Oh, you needn't be callin'
a lowly ship's cook ''sir.''

369
00:23:32,720 --> 00:23:36,679
Long John Silver,
at your humble service.

370
00:23:36,760 --> 00:23:39,354
We're just cabin boys,
Mr Silver.

371
00:23:39,440 --> 00:23:43,115
Long John to his friends.

372
00:23:43,200 --> 00:23:44,792
And believe me, lad...

373
00:23:44,880 --> 00:23:49,112
a friend you can trust
is worth his weight in gold.

374
00:23:49,200 --> 00:23:53,751
There's many a dark-hearted
scoundrel in these ports.

375
00:23:53,840 --> 00:23:55,831
Well, what do you mean?
Pirates?

376
00:23:55,920 --> 00:23:58,354
- Shh!
- Pirates! That's rich!

377
00:23:58,440 --> 00:24:01,273
Pirates? What an imagination.
Give me a cracker.

378
00:24:01,360 --> 00:24:04,477
Allow me to introduce
my pet lobster Polly.

379
00:24:04,560 --> 00:24:06,710
Pieces of eight!
Pieces of eight!

380
00:24:06,800 --> 00:24:08,631
Raised him
from a fingerling, I did.

381
00:24:08,720 --> 00:24:12,156
As fine a crustacean
as a man could ask for.

382
00:24:12,240 --> 00:24:15,198
B-But I thought sailors
had talking parrots as pets.

383
00:24:15,280 --> 00:24:17,430
Talking parrots?

384
00:24:17,520 --> 00:24:21,752
What an imagination.
First pirates, now talking parrots?

385
00:24:21,840 --> 00:24:25,753
What's next? A singing, dancing mouse
with his own amusement park?

386
00:24:25,840 --> 00:24:27,876
That's enough now, Polly.
Go on! Shoo!

387
00:24:30,960 --> 00:24:34,953
Right, me hearties. I'm gonna give you
a cook's tour of this fine ship.

388
00:24:35,040 --> 00:24:37,395
If you're gonna be the cook
on this ship, Mr Silver...

389
00:24:37,480 --> 00:24:39,835
I am definitely gonna need
bigger pants.

390
00:24:46,640 --> 00:24:48,471
What's the matter, lads?

391
00:24:51,600 --> 00:24:53,079
Oh, that?

392
00:24:53,160 --> 00:24:58,359
Lost that timber-fighting brigands
off Madagascar under Admiral Hawke.

393
00:24:58,440 --> 00:25:02,399
There's many a man lost a leg and worse
in the service of the king.

394
00:25:02,480 --> 00:25:07,031
Why, look what a cannibal
took off me...

395
00:25:07,120 --> 00:25:09,759
in exchange for me own life.

396
00:25:17,520 --> 00:25:19,715
Oh, you're a fine pair, lads.
That you are.

397
00:25:19,800 --> 00:25:22,917
Bright as buttons,
the lot of ye.

398
00:25:23,000 --> 00:25:25,798
- All hands on deck!
- Come on, then, lads.

399
00:25:27,120 --> 00:25:31,033
Chop-chop! Look lively now.
The captain will be here soon.

400
00:25:32,120 --> 00:25:33,792
Chop-chop.

401
00:25:36,320 --> 00:25:40,916
- Who's that?
- That is Mr Arrow, the first mate,

402
00:25:42,960 --> 00:25:45,793
The captain approaches.

403
00:25:50,000 --> 00:25:52,560
Move aside! Make way!
Make ready for the captain!

404
00:25:52,640 --> 00:25:54,676
Lollygaggers will suffer
his wrath!

405
00:25:54,760 --> 00:25:56,591
Wrath? I-Is this captain
bad-tempered?

406
00:25:56,680 --> 00:26:00,593
Is he bad-tempered?
The man is a raging volcano...

407
00:26:00,680 --> 00:26:04,434
tormented by inner demons the likes
of which mere mortals cannot fathom.

408
00:26:04,520 --> 00:26:06,556
He's got demons? Cool!

409
00:26:18,920 --> 00:26:20,831
Maniac!

410
00:26:43,720 --> 00:26:46,029
Heigh-ho, everyone.

411
00:26:46,120 --> 00:26:48,634
- What-- That--
- That's the raging volcano?

412
00:26:48,720 --> 00:26:52,474
- He's a frog.
- Maybe he gets hopping mad.

413
00:26:52,560 --> 00:26:54,471
Hopping mad.

414
00:27:01,800 --> 00:27:06,590
Piping aboard
Captain Abraham Smollett.

415
00:27:07,440 --> 00:27:09,351
Good day, Mr Arrow.

416
00:27:13,440 --> 00:27:16,557
I knew it.
He's furious.

417
00:27:16,640 --> 00:27:18,551
- Ah, you there!
- Me?

418
00:27:18,640 --> 00:27:21,916
You were in charge of railing dust.
Thirty lashes, and then

419
00:27:22,680 --> 00:27:27,879
- I didn't say that, Mr Arrow.
- I was anticipating your whim, sir.

420
00:27:29,200 --> 00:27:30,997
Oh. You must be
the cabin boys.

421
00:27:31,080 --> 00:27:33,230
- Yes, sir!
- Which one of you is Hawkins?

422
00:27:33,320 --> 00:27:35,151
I am, sir.

423
00:27:35,240 --> 00:27:37,390
I knew your father,Jim.
He was a good man.

424
00:27:37,480 --> 00:27:39,948
Thank you, sir.

425
00:27:40,040 --> 00:27:44,511
Well, this is shapin' up
to be a fine voyage, lads.

426
00:27:44,600 --> 00:27:47,068
Oh, yes, indeed.

427
00:27:49,920 --> 00:27:52,480
One leg,Jim.
Count 'em. One.

428
00:27:52,560 --> 00:27:56,348
- Remember what Billy Bones said.
- Oh, Gonzo, he seems all right.

429
00:27:56,440 --> 00:28:00,319
I mean, Long John's only a cook.
How dangerous could he be?

430
00:28:00,400 --> 00:28:03,198
Well, I don't know, but I--
Wait a minute. Where's Rizzo?

431
00:28:03,280 --> 00:28:06,238
Enjoy your cruise, sir.
Next!

432
00:28:06,320 --> 00:28:09,869
All right, folks, have your cheques
made out to ''Rat Tours Limited.''

433
00:28:09,960 --> 00:28:13,077
Remember, we put
the rat in ''pirate.''

434
00:28:14,520 --> 00:28:16,431
Why, thank you,
Mr Plagueman. Next!

435
00:28:16,520 --> 00:28:19,671
- Rizzo, what are you doing?
- What? Oh, this.

436
00:28:19,760 --> 00:28:21,591
Well, I figure
if the treasure map's a dud...

437
00:28:21,680 --> 00:28:25,639
the trip won't be a total loss,
financially speaking.

438
00:28:25,720 --> 00:28:29,110
Well, the wind seems to be freshening.
The tide is with us.

439
00:28:29,200 --> 00:28:32,033
Mr Arrow,
this voyage has begun.

440
00:28:32,120 --> 00:28:36,318
This voyage has begun!
Raise the gangplank!

441
00:28:36,400 --> 00:28:38,834
- Right, lads!
- Let go forward line!

442
00:28:38,920 --> 00:28:42,390
Let go aft line.
Hard to starboard.

443
00:28:42,480 --> 00:28:45,119
Any man caught dawdling
will be shot on sight.

444
00:28:45,200 --> 00:28:47,156
- I didn't say that.
- I was just paraphrasing.

445
00:28:47,240 --> 00:28:51,836
- Mr Arrow, just set the sails.
- Set the sails!

446
00:28:52,880 --> 00:28:54,791
Hey, where's my camera?

447
00:28:54,880 --> 00:28:58,395
- I'll miss you! I said I'll miss you!
- We'll send postcards!

448
00:28:58,480 --> 00:29:00,675
- Goodbye!
- Goodbye!

449
00:29:07,920 --> 00:29:10,480
<i>When the course is laid</i>
<i>and the anchor's weighed</i>

450
00:29:10,560 --> 00:29:13,028
<i>A sailor's blood</i>
<i>begins racing</i>

451
00:29:13,120 --> 00:29:15,953
<i>With our hearts unbound</i>
<i>and our flag unfurled</i>

452
00:29:16,040 --> 00:29:18,793
<i>We're underway and off</i>
<i>to see the world</i>

